## 🛠️ **Basic Git Operations**

### **1. Setting Up Git**
```bash
# Install Git (one-time setup)
# Download from git-scm.com

# Configure your identity
git config --global user.name "Your Name"
git config --global user.email "your.email@example.com"

# Check configuration
git config --list
```

### **2. Starting a Repository**

#### **Option A: Create New Repository**
```bash
# Initialize Git in your project folder
cd my-project
git init

# Check status (see what Git is tracking)
git status
```

#### **Option B: Clone Existing Repository**
```bash
# Download a project from GitHub
git clone https://github.com/username/repository.git
```

### **3. Making Changes (The Core Workflow)**

```bash
# 1. Check what files have changed
git status

# 2. Add files to staging area (prepare for commit)
git add filename.txt           # Add specific file
git add .                      # Add all files
git add *.js                   # Add all JavaScript files

# 3. Commit changes (save snapshot)
git commit -m "feat: add login functionality"

# 4. View history
git log                        # Full history
git log --oneline              # Compact history
git log --graph                # Visual history
```

### **4. Working with Branches**

```bash
# List branches
git branch                      # Local branches
git branch -r                   # Remote branches

# Create and switch branches
git branch feature-login        # Create branch
git checkout feature-login       # Switch to branch
# OR do both at once:
git checkout -b feature-login

# Merge branches
git checkout main               # Switch to main
git merge feature-login         # Merge feature into main

# Delete branch
git branch -d feature-login     # Delete local branch
```

### **5. Synchronizing with GitHub**

```bash
# Connect local repo to GitHub
git remote add origin https://github.com/username/repo.git

# Push changes to GitHub
git push origin main            # Upload commits
git push --all                  # Push all branches

# Download changes from GitHub
git pull origin main            # Download and merge
git fetch origin                # Download without merging

# First-time push (with -u to set upstream)
git push -u origin main
```

### **6. Undoing Changes**

```bash
# Undo staging (before commit)
git reset filename.txt          # Unstage file
git reset                       # Unstage all

# Undo commit (keep changes)
git reset --soft HEAD~1         # Undo last commit, keep changes

# Undo commit (discard changes)
git reset --hard HEAD~1         # Completely remove last commit

# Undo changes in working directory
git checkout -- filename.txt    # Discard changes to file
git restore filename.txt        # Newer way (Git 2.23+)
```

### **7. Stashing (Temporary Save)**

```bash
# Save work-in-progress
git stash                       # Stash changes
git stash save "message"        # Stash with description

# Apply stashed changes
git stash pop                   # Apply and remove from stash
git stash apply                 # Apply but keep in stash

# Manage stashes
git stash list                  # View all stashes
git stash drop                  # Remove last stash
git stash clear                 # Remove all stashes
```

