## 🔄 **Common Workflows**

### **Workflow 1: Solo Developer**
```bash
# Morning
git pull origin main

# Work on feature
git checkout -b new-feature
# ... make changes ...
git add .
git commit -m "feat: add awesome feature"
git push origin new-feature

# Create PR on GitHub
# Merge when ready

# Clean up
git checkout main
git pull origin main
git branch -d new-feature
```

### **Workflow 2: Team Collaboration**
```bash
# Before starting work
git checkout main
git pull origin main
git checkout -b feature/your-task

# While working
git add specific-file.js
git commit -m "feat: implement core logic"

# Before pushing, update from main
git checkout main
git pull origin main
git checkout feature/your-task
git merge main

# Push and create PR
git push origin feature/your-task
# Create PR on GitHub with description
```

### **Workflow 3: Handling Conflicts**
```bash
# When git pull shows conflicts
git pull origin main
# CONFLICT in file.js

# Fix conflicts manually in editor
git add file.js
git commit -m "merge: resolve conflicts in file.js"
git push origin feature/your-task
```

